ZH: 要是你再晚一点到，我们可能会错过火车。
EN: If you arrive any later, we might miss the train.

ZH: 要是我有更多时间，我会去旅行。
EN: If I had more time, I would travel.

ZH: 要是你不告诉我，我怎么会知道呢？
EN: If you don't tell me, how would I know?

ZH: 要是她在这里，我们就能开始会议了。
EN: If she were here, we could start the meeting.

ZH: 要是明天天气好，我们可以去爬山。
EN: If the weather is good tomorrow, we can go hiking.

ZH: 要是你帮我，我就能完成这个任务。
EN: If you help me, I can complete this task.

ZH: 要是这个计划失败了，我们将不得不重新开始。
EN: If this plan fails, we will have to start over.

ZH: 要是他来了，请告诉我一声。
EN: If he comes, please let me know.

ZH: 要是没有你的帮助，我不知道该怎么办。
EN: If it weren't for your help, I wouldn't know what to do.

ZH: 要是你能来参加我的生日派对，我会很高兴。
EN: If you can come to my birthday party, I would be really happy.

ZH: 要是你不提醒我，我可能会忘记。
EN: If you don't remind me, I might forget.

ZH: 要是你能说得更慢一点，我会更容易理解。
EN: If you could speak slower, I would understand better.

ZH: 要是他能赢得比赛，他将获得一笔奖金。
EN: If he can win the competition, he will receive a bonus.

ZH: 要是我成为总经理，我会推行一些改革。
EN: If I became the general manager, I would implement some reforms.

ZH: 要是你努力学习，你一定会成功的。
EN: If you study hard, you will definitely succeed.

ZH: 要是他没有交通工具，他会步行去学校。
EN: If he doesn't have any transportation, he will walk to school.

ZH: 要是你不骗我，我会相信你的话。
EN: If you don't lie to me, I will believe what you say.

ZH: 要是明天下雨，我们将取消野餐计划。
EN: If it rains tomorrow, we will cancel the picnic plan.

ZH: 要是我有足够的钱，我会买一辆新车。
EN: If I had enough money, I would buy a new car.

ZH: 要是你再这样说，我会生气的。
EN: If you say that again, I will get angry.
